<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 4/4. Bold processional hymn. LH "33" triads, RH light thirds/fifths.
- Eb (non-diatonic in bar 7) → substituted as Em (③m) for diatonic purity.
- F#° substituted as D (②).

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH holds D3 common tone through G and D7 chords.
- RH climbs to G5 at bar 5 then descends to D5.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Strong opening; builds to bar 5 climax; steady descent to G close bar 10.
-->
